<section id="how-it-works" class="bg-wa-surface-raised px-6 py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[640px]">
    <h2>How it works</h2>

    <p>
      Design Bridge sits between your running UI and your AI agent. You leave feedback directly on
      the page, the agent reads it via MCP, and changes land in your source files.
    </p>

    <ol class="mt-8 space-y-6">
      <li class="flex gap-6">
        <span
          class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-wa-brand-fill-normal text-[11px] font-semibold text-wa-brand-on-normal"
          >1</span
        >
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium">Select an element</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-wa-text-quiet">
            Hold <kbd
              class="rounded border border-wa-surface-border px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs"
              >Alt</kbd
            > and click any element in your browser. A comment thread opens attached to that element.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-6">
        <span
          class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-wa-brand-fill-normal text-[11px] font-semibold text-wa-brand-on-normal"
          >2</span
        >
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium">Write a comment</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-wa-text-quiet">
            Describe what you want to change. The comment is stored locally and surfaced to your
            agent through the MCP server.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-6">
        <span
          class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-wa-brand-fill-normal text-[11px] font-semibold text-wa-brand-on-normal"
          >3</span
        >
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium">Get a live tweak</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-wa-text-quiet">
            The agent can reply with a knob — a live control that updates your source file on the
            fly so you can try values without switching to an editor.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flex gap-6">
        <span
          class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-wa-brand-fill-normal text-[11px] font-semibold text-wa-brand-on-normal"
          >4</span
        >
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium">Accept or discard</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-wa-text-quiet">
            Keep the change by accepting it — the file is updated permanently. Discard to restore
            the original. Either way the thread stays as a record.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
